<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blazers Center Sabonis Hurts Foot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Portland Trail Blazers center Arvydas
Sabonis severely sprained his right foot Wednesday night when he
fell awkwardly after being bumped by Detroit's Christian Laettner.
</P>
<P>
   The injury occurred with four minutes left in the third quarter,
and the Blazers ahead 75-64.
</P>
<P>
   Sabonis got a long lob pass from Rasheed Wallace near the
basket, and Laettner nudged him with his right arm. Sabonis' left
foot slipped, and the 7-foot-3 player fell to the floor, his right
foot pinned underneath.
</P>
<P>
   Sabonis howled in pain, and he was helped from the floor by
teammates, unable to put any weight on his right leg.
</P>
<P>
   Laettner was called for a personal foul.
</P>
<P>
   Sabonis had 15 points and seven rebounds when he was hurt.
</P>
</TEXT>
