Palestinians Get Web Designation
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Palestinians will get their independence in cyberspace
before they get a country of their own. A separate Internet domain name for
Palestinian Web sites won approval Wednesday, meaning Palestinian Web sites
could begin using their own suffix, ''ps,'' the same way Israelis have used
''il'' for years. The two-letter country codes are similar to the function of
''com'' in Internet addresses. The U.S. government approved the recommendation
from the Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers, a private group
overseeing the world's Internet address system.
