per game, sustained the injury with .2 seconds left in the first half while
racing the clock to take a shot. Julie Fie, the Suns director of media
relations, said Kidd fractured a bone (medial malleolus) high in the right ankle
and will have surgery on Thursday. She said Kidd is ''questionable for the
playoffs.''
