<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Money Funds Rose in Latest Week  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Assets of the nation's retail money market
mutual funds rose by $891.1 million in the latest week to $998.37
billion, the Investment Company Institute said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Assets of taxable money market funds in the retail category fell
by $320.5 million to $829.70 billion for the week ended Wednesday,
the Washington-based mutual fund trade group said. Tax-exempt fund
assets rose by $1.21 billion to $168.67 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Assets of institutional money market funds rose by $2.89 billion
to $710.22 billion for the same period. Among institutional funds,
taxable money market fund assets rose by $3.18 billion to $658.18
billion; assets of tax-exempt funds fell by $289.0 million to
$52.04 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Total money market assets stood at $1.709 trillion for the week.
</P>
<P>
   Assets for the previous week were revised to $1.705 trillion to
reflect reporting errors and a change in the number of funds
reporting.
</P>
<P>
   The seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds rose in
the week ended Tuesday to 5.32 percent from 5.28 percent the
previous week, said IBC's Money Fund Report, a trade journal
published in Ashland, Mass., by IBC Financial Data Inc. The 30-day
average yield rose to 5.28 percent from 5.26 percent, IBC Financial
Data said.
</P>
<P>
   The seven-day compounded yield rose to 5.46 percent from 5.42
percent the previous week, and the 30-day compounded yield rose to
5.42 percent from 5.40 percent, IBC Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
   The average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was
48 days, unchanged from the previous week, IBC Financial Data said.
</P>
<P>
   The online service bankrate.com said its survey of 100 leading
commercial banks, savings and loan associations and savings banks
in the nation's 10 largest markets showed the annual percentage
yield available on money market accounts was 2.04 percent as of
Wednesday unchanged from a week earlier.
</P>
<P>
   The North Palm Beach, Fla.-based unit of Intelligent Life Corp.
said the annual percentage yield available on interest-bearing
checking accounts was 0.82 percent, down from 0.83 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Bankrate.com said the annual percentage yield was 4.85 percent
on six-month certificates of deposit, unchanged from the previous
week. Yields were 5.31 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 5.28 percent;
5.56 percent on 2{-year CDs, unchanged; and 5.95 percent on 5-year
CDs, up from 5.93 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
