<HEADLINE> Poll of Candidates' Personalities  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Some results from a new poll by the Pew Research
Center for the
People &AMP; the Press about public perception of the presidential
candidates' personal qualities. When results don't total 100
percent, the remainder either didn't know or declined to answer.
<TEXT>
<P>
   What do you like most about the following candidate, his
personality, his leadership ability, his experience or his stand on
the issues?
</P>
<P>
   Voters who chose Al Gore said they most liked his:
</P>
<P>
   -- Personality, 10 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Leadership, 14 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Experience, 28 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Stand on issues, 40 percent
</P>
<P>
