</P>
<P>
   -- Personality, 14 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Leadership, 24 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Experience, 10 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Stand on issues, 42 percent
</P>
<P>
   What do you like least about the following candidate, his
personality, his leadership ability, his experience or his stand on
the issues?
</P>
<P>
   Voters who chose Gore said they disliked Bush most for his:
</P>
<P>
   -- Personality, 33 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Leadership, 8 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Experience, 13 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Stands on issues, 35 percent
</P>
<P>
   (The percentage who disliked Bush most for his personality
increased from 19 percent in October.)
</P>
<P>
   Voters who chose Bush said they disliked Gore most for his:
</P>
<P>
   -- Personality, 22 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Leadership, 20 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Experience, 5 percent
</P>
<P>
   -- Stands on issues, 43 percent
</P>
<P>
   (The percentages on Gore haven't changed significantly since
October.)
</P>
<P>
   Please tell me what one word best describes your impression of
the following candidate? (includes top six choices and the number
of times word was mentioned by a respondent, not percentages)
</P>
