<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
Thursday, March 23, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dow Ends Up 253.16; Nasdaq Gains 75.94
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks advanced broadly today, carrying the Dow
over 11,000 for the first time in seven weeks, as a rally in
high-tech issues spread throughout Wall Street. Microsoft touched
off the advance after The Wall Street Journal reported that the
software maker and the government were accelerating talks toward
resolving their longstanding antitrust case. The Dow Jones
industrial average rose 253.16 today to 11,119.86. It last closed
above 11,000 on Feb. 3. On the New York Stock Exchange, advancing
issues outnumbered declining issues 1,834- 1,159. The high-tech
dominated Nasdaq composite index rose 75.94 to 4,940.69.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures as of Thursday's close:
Dow Industrials:        11,119.86  + 253.16
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1,834  Declines 1,159  Unchgd  485
NYSE Volume:       1,068,190,040
Most Active NYSE issue:         Compaq Computer29]   - 2|  
