<HEADLINE> 8th Death in Day Care Vehicle Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TROIS-RIVIERES, Quebec (AP) -- A 4-year-old boy died Thursday of
head and abdominal injuries suffered in a road accident last week
that killed seven other pre-schoolers, including his 2-year-old
sister.
</P>
<P>
   The March 16 accident in a rural community 70 miles north of
Montreal occurred when a minivan transporting the children on a
day-care outing swerved into the path of an oncoming minivan.
</P>
<P>
   Both drivers survived, but seven of the children aged 2 to 5
years old died. The victims included Stacy Roy, whose brother Kevin
died Thursday at Trois-Rivieres regional hospital, a spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
   Jeanne Auger, the day-care center operator who was driving the
van, was released from an area hospital Wednesday after being
treated for minor injuries and shock. One of the children killed in
the accident was her 5-year-old son.
</P>
