<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Suburban Pittsburgh  </HEADLINE>
By TODD SPANGLER, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONROEVILLE, Pa. (AP) -- Two people were shot to death Thursday
and a woman was wounded inside a home that caught fire, authorities
said. The wounded woman rushed bleeding into a neighboring
business.
</P>
<P>
   ''We believe it to have been sparked by a domestic violence
situation,'' said George Polnar, police chief in Monroeville, 15
miles east of Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   Police believe a man may have killed his girlfriend and wounded
a woman, then set the house on fire and killed himself, Polnar
said, but he couldn't yet confirm that scenario.
</P>
<P>
   A woman who had been shot ran into The Money Tree, a mortgage
company next door to the house, and asked employees to call 911.
</P>
<P>
   ''She said, 'This guy shot me,''' said Diana Kugliari, a
mortgage consultant. ''She said he said, 'I'll let you live.'''
</P>
<P>
   Another Money Tree employee, Tony Nicolazzo, said the woman,
with blood on her face and hands, ''told us that the boyfriend of
the girl who lived next door was in the house and shot the girl.''
</P>
<P>
   ''She apparently got out of the house through a window and came
over here,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The victim, Jennifer Filar, 23, was treated for gunshot wounds
to her neck, face and hands and was awake and alert in a Pittsburgh
hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The house sat alongside a four-lane road in a middle-class
neighborhood of homes and businesses.
</P>
<P>
   Police and emergency workers were called to the address in
February, when one person there was hospitalized for a psychiatric
evaluation, said Doug Cole, assistant Monroeville police chief. He
declined to say whether that person was killed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The dead were identified as Anne Lazzara, 25, and Nigel Francis,
33.
</P>
</TEXT>
