<HEADLINE> Tokyo Shares Rise in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar slipped against the yen early Friday as
investors adjusted their dollar positions ahead of the weekend.
Tokyo's benchmark stock index rose moderately.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar bought 107.28 yen, down 0.10 yen from late Thursday
in Tokyo and also below its late New York level of 107.32.
</P>
<P>
   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 27.31
points, or 0.14 percent, to 19,731.91 points in the first 30
minutes of trading. On Thursday, the average closed down 28.99
points, or 0.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
   In currency dealings, traders said the dollar edged lower
against the yen as investors squared their dollar positions ahead
of the weekend in the absence of major market-moving news.
</P>
<P>
   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 104.05 yen, up from
103.32 yen late Thursday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   On the stock market, prices were mixed in early trading as many
institutional investors avoided making significant moves before the
fiscal year-end book closing.
</P>
<P>
   Japan's new fiscal year begins on April 1.
</P>
<P>
   In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average rose 253.16 points
to 11,119.86 at Thursday's close.
</P>
<P>
   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was down 4.00 points, or 0.24 percent, to 1,647.55
points. The TOPIX closed down 6.77 points, or 0.41 percent, the day
before.
</P>
<P>
   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond was
unquoted in early trading. On Thursday, it settled at 1.8450
percent and its price stood at 100.47.
</P>
</TEXT>
