<HEADLINE> School Driver Accused of Molesting  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANDERSON, Ind. (AP) -- A school bus driver has been charged with
repeatedly molesting a 9-year-old passenger.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffrey Lee Holding appeared before a judge Thursday to face
seven child molestation charges, punishable by 20 to 50 years in
prison.
</P>
<P>
   He was arrested Wednesday and remained in jail in lieu of
$100,000 bond. Holding was fired after the girl told school
officials about the alleged abuse two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   Holding, 46, of Muncie, is accused of molesting the girl during
a seven-week period that began early this year.
</P>
<P>
   The girl was the first stop on Holding's morning route,
authorities said. After picking her up, Holding allegedly pulled
the bus to the side of a road, walked back to her seat, sat beside
her and molested her, according to court documents. Holding then
would drive on to his next stops, picking up the rest of his
passengers.
</P>
<P>
   Holding has denied molesting the girl, court documents say.
</P>
<P>
   A background check done by Madison Bus Co., which employed
Holding, showed he had no criminal history, said Larry Arms, the
school district's transportation director.
</P>
