<HEADLINE> European Soccer Roundup  </HEADLINE>
By STEPHEN WADE, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   The UEFA Cup semifinals will have some fresh faces after
Turkey's Galatasaray, France's Lens, and English teams Leeds and
Arsenal reached the final four Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Galatasaray, motivated by a bill in parliament that would pay
the club $5 million for reaching the semifinals -- and $9 million
for winning the cup -- beat Mallorca 2-1 and advanced 6-2 in the
home-and-home, total-goals series. It's unclear when the bill will
be debated.
</P>
<P>
   Galatasaray became the first Turkish team to reach a European
cup semifinal since it did so in the 1989 Champions Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Leeds, which won the UEFA Cup in 1968 and 1971, lost 2-1 at
Slavia Prague but advanced on a 4-2 aggregate.
</P>
<P>
   Arsenal defeated Werder Bremen 4-2 on three goals by Ray Parlour
to advance 6-2. The Gunners, who won the UEFA Cup in 1970, are
hoping to win Europe's No. 2 club competition after being
eliminated from the first phase of the Champions Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Lens beat Celta de Vigo 2-1 to reach its first UEFA Cup
semifinal after a scoreless tie last week in Spain.
</P>
<P>
   The draw for next month's semifinals is Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Italy, which has won eight of the last 11 UEFA Cups, saw all of
its entrants eliminated in the round of 16. Parma won the UEFA Cup
last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
