<HEADLINE> Bucks 105, Pacers 84  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Sam Cassell scored 30 points and Ray Allen
added 26 as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Indiana Pacers 105-84 on
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Bucks, who also got 21 points from Tim Thomas, held the
Pacers to 38 percent shooting in snapping a six-game road losing
streak.
</P>
<P>
   Cassell, who hit 11 of 16 field goals and all eight free throws,
scored 13 points in the first half to help the Bucks build a 62-40
lead at the break.
</P>
<P>
   Milwaukee handed Indiana its fourth loss in 35 games at Conseco
Field House. Jalen Rose led the Pacers with 22 points, while Reggie
Miller had 16 points as the Pacers lost for just the fourth time in
35 home games.
</P>
<P>
   Milwaukee hit 51 percent of its field goals, while Indiana hit
just 37.5 percent. The Bucks had a 47-36 rebounding edge.
</P>
<P>
   Although the Pacers shot 71 percent in the third quarter -- 10 of
16 from the field -- they still trailed the Bucks 85-68 entering the
fourth quarter.
Notes: Milwaukee won for just the sixth time in its last 20 games.
... Indiana center Rik Smits, who hit 50 percent from the field and
averaged 18 points during the Pacers' four-game winning streak, was
just 1-of-5 Thursday, scoring two points. ... Ray Allen, the only
Bucks' player to start all 68 games this season, has scored double
figures in 71 straight games. ... As a starter in the Pacers' last
six games, forward Austin Croshere has led his team in rebounding,
averaging 11.2 per game. ... Tim Thomas is averaging 18 points in
his last 11 games.
</P>
