<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NC State 77, Mississippi 54  </HEADLINE>
By ELIZABETH A. DAVIS, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- Kenny Inge scored 17 points and Damien
Wilkins added 16 Thursday night as North Carolina State advanced to
the semifinals of the NIT with a 77-54 victory over Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   N.C. State (20-12), in its fourth straight NIT, reached the
semifinals for the first time since 1978, when the Wolfpack lost to
Texas in the title game.
</P>
<P>
   N.C. State will play the winner of Friday's California-Wake
Forest game.
</P>
<P>
   N.C. State reached 20 victories for the first time since 1991.
</P>
<P>
   The Wolfpack went ahead 3-2 on Anthony Grundy's 3-pointer a
minute into the game and never relinquished the lead.
</P>
<P>
   Ole Miss (19-14) trimmed the lead to 40-31 after Jason
Harrison's 3-pointer with 16:59 remaining and then to 43-36 after
Rahim Lockhart's putback with 13:26 to go, only to have a technical
foul derail the comeback.
</P>
<P>
   After Wilkins hit two free throws, Ole Miss' Marcus Hicks was
given a technical for slamming the ball after a foul was called.
Archie Miller hit both free throws and Wilkins dunked Miller's miss
for a 49-36 lead.
</P>
<P>
   N.C. State jumped to a 23-7 lead with 10:57 to go in the first
half after Inge made two free throws and maintained a double-digit
lead the rest of the first half.
</P>
<P>
   Flanigan hit consecutive 3s to cut N.C. State's lead to 32-22
with 1:33 left in the first half, but the Wolfpack held the Rebels
scoreless after that to lead 38-22 at halftime.
</P>
</TEXT>
