<HEADLINE> Capitals 4, Rangers 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Jeff Halpern scored two goals, and Olaf Kolzig
made 27 saves to lead the Washington Capitals to a 4-1 victory over
the New York Rangers on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Adam Oates had a goal to extend his scoring streak to eight
games, and Chris Simon scored for the Capitals who are 10-2-1 in
their last 13.
</P>
<P>
   Mike York scored for the Rangers, who are 1-4-1 in their last
six.
</P>
<P>
   Kolzig was brilliant in making tough saves on Tim Taylor and
Brian Leetch at the end of 3-on-1 breaks and robbing Leetch on a
power-play point shot with less than six minutes remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Simon gave Washington a 1-0 lead at 8:05 of the first period
with his 28th goal of the season. Simon took a pass from Glen
Metropolit in the left corner and wristed a shot from 10 feet out
that beat Rangers goalie Kirk McLean high to the stick side.
</P>
