<HEADLINE> Red Wings 6, Predators 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Sergei Fedorov had a goal and two
assists, and the Detroit Red Wings scored four times in the second
period to beat the Nashville Predators 6-3 Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Stacy Roest, Mathieu Dandenault, Larry Murphy, Tomas Holmstrom
and Brent Gilchrist also scored for Detroit, which won for just the
second time in five games.
</P>
<P>
   Tom Fitzgerald, Vitali Yachmenev and Patric Kjellberg scored for
Nashville, which fell to 13-21-3 at home -- the worst home winning
percentage in the Western Conference.
</P>
<P>
   The Predators dominated the Red Wings in the first period,
outshooting them 18-7 and outscoring them 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Fitzgerald scored on a rebound at 8:16, but Roest briefly tied
it on another rebound.
</P>
<P>
   Then Yachmenev put the Predators up 2-1 with a slap shot that
seemed to handcuff Red Wings goalie Ken Wregget. Kjellberg
connected on a two-man advantage to give Nashville a 3-1 lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Wings, who looked sluggish at first after playing an
overtime game the night before against Calgary, stormed back in the
second on Thursday. They scored three goals on five shots in the
first 9:23 to take a 4-3 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Dandenault connected at 1:40 off a rebound, and Murphy scored
off Pat Verbeek's cross-ice pass behind Predators goalie Tomas
Vokoun at 4:28 to tie it. Fedorov finally put Detroit ahead 4-3 on
a breakaway at 9:23.
</P>
<P>
   Holmstrom continued Detroit's scoring spurt at 15:38, poking the
rebound of Fedorov's shot past Vokoun to give the Red Wings a 5-3
lead.
</P>
<P>
   Gilchrist scored the final goal into an empty net at 18:53 of
the third.
</P>
<P>
   One night after collecting his 500th NHL goal, Verbeek had a
pair of assists to give him 509 for his career.
</P>
<P>
   Detroit's Brendan Shanahan sat out with the flu.
</P>
</TEXT>
