<HEADLINE> Search Continues For Mass. Kids  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WORTHINGTON, Mass. (AP) -- State and local authorities were
searching Thursday night for four missing girls who took a walk in
the late afternoon and failed to return.
</P>
<P>
   A 12-year-old baby sitter and three girls -- ages 3, 4 and 5 --
went for a walk at about 5 p.m. in a rural, wooded area, said state
Trooper Michael Martin.
</P>
<P>
   Martin said the kids promised to be back in half an hour and
didn't return.
</P>
<P>
   State police Lt. Paul Maloney said that by late evening about
100 people had converged on the search site in western
Massachusetts, along with police dogs and two police helicopters.
</P>
<P>
   ''There's certainly concern,'' Maloney said. ''The temperatures
could certainly drop.''
</P>
<P>
   Worthington, population 1,200, is about 115 miles west of
Boston.
</P>
</TEXT>
